ce energy is $<\n10^{52}$erg. A hypothetical population of transient sources has to be more\ncommon than $10^{-5}\\text{Mpc}^{-3}\\text{yr}^{-1}$\n($5\\times10^{-8}\\text{Mpc}^{-3}\\text{yr}^{-1}$ for the $E^{-2.13}$ spectrum) to\naccount for the complete astrophysical neutrino flux.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Jul 2018 18:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 1 Aug 2018 08:53:10 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 27 Feb 2019 12:29:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-28"}
